						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#157;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;3 (Topolomemory 3) is a stand-alone expansion to &amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#157;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188; (TOPOLOMEMORY). It follows the same gameplay but introduces even more complex shapes, including English words and detailed images. The game also has an improved quality cardstock to the original edition. It can be played alone, or mixed in with Topolomemory, and/or &amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#157;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#146; (Topolomemory 2).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#157;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188; (TOPOLOMEMORY) is a Japanese card game based on the traditional matching game Karuta.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Topolomemory is a concentration game in which you have to match shapes using the principles of  Topology. In it's basic form, topology shows us that a doughnut is the same as a coffee mug.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Lay out the tiles with various images on them and whoever most quickly identifies pairs that match topologically gets to collect the pair. The player with the most pairs wins the game. The game game be played by more than five players, especially in teams.&amp;#10;User summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
